spanGrp.span: Me, I will speak here with Richard, I will tell a story
anin gidabalol aa gandaw Richard gabalol hadis
ànìn gìdàbàlól àà gàndàw Ríchàrd gàbàlól hàdís
mimi nitaongea nikiwa na Richard nitaongea hadithi
In the old days, the Asimjeeg
That were living in Law and one day they were told by Ewanda
imuch gobit laaw imuch gwayesh ewand
ìmúch gòbìt lààw ìmúch gwàyésh éwànd
wakawa wanaishi musoma siku moja wakaambiwa na Ewanda
We started the trip and when we reached the path we saw fog and the land became dark
geang'et aa gesawagany is geafk aa isihid naweed geada lanid lanid gamusanit darorta
'géang'ét àâ gésàwàgàny ìs géfk àà ìsíhíd nàwéd géadà làníd làníd gàmúsànít dàrórtá'
tukaanza safari na tukifia njiani tunaona ukungu ukungu nchi imekuwa giza
It came and often it would eat people, even a hundred
gwajag geaw aa is gwanugd fug nyit miya
gwàjàg géaw àà ìs gwànùgd fùg nyít míyà
inakuja na huwa anawameza kuwameza hata watu mia
He's hitting people and eating even a thousand people
gwalas aa gwanugd fug nyit aluf moj
gwàlàs àà gwànúgd fúg nyít àlúf mòj
ninapiga na kuwameza hata watu elfu moja
Now this Aqasheda is very harsh and one day they were told "If you want to kill this Awasheeda,"
sasa aqashed ang'an diya imuch geyesh ijaabar aqashan
'sasa àqàshéd àng''àn díyà ìmúch géyésh íjààbàr àqàshàn'
sasa hiyo aqasheda ni mkali sana siku moja wakaambiwa kama mnataka kumwua huyo aqasheda
"If you want to kill it, Ewanda will look for this Awasheeda"
gowil ijaabar ewanjanj gowil barband was aqashed
gòwìl íjààbàr éwànjànj gòwìl bàrbànd wàs àqàshéd
mkitaka kumpika huyo Ewanda mtafuteni mtu ambaye ni Aqasheda
"He will attack him and strangle him and he will die" because he has already killed people
gigawut aa gigawawsiny aa muhoqd aa qamewabgidab godulg buneed
gìgàwút àà gígàwàwsíny àà múhòqd àà qàméwàbgìdàb gòdúlg bùnééd
atamlenga na atachanganya na shingo na atakufa kwa sababu alishawamaliza watu
They ran from Law and these dark clouds came with them
gijesalunan oshu law gewayanayi lanidan getahanani
gíjésàlúnàn òshú làw géwàyànàyí lànídàn gétàhànàní
wanakimbia kutoka huko musoma na hiyo ukungu wanakujanayo
Later the people who didn't go there went to Mbulu
kesho watu ambao hawaendi huko wanaenda mbulu
And now at this time Awasheed was already killed
ab hij aa geabara aqashan eee
àb hìj àà géabàrà aqàshàn ééé
na sasa hapo hiyo aqashan imeshauliwa
He had already been killed and finished by people, he had a power to swallow a hundred people at one time
geabar ha qomew aa godulgw buneen gwanukwid fug nyit miya ab aweachanjag
géabàr hà qòméw àà gòdúlgw bùnéén gwànúkwíd fúg nyìt mìyà àb àwéachànjàg
na meshapigwa na kuuwawa na aliwamaliza watu,anauwezo wa kuwameza watu mia kwa mara moja
He's already been hit and killed
Another day the Asimjeeg came to live in Someega and others who didn't go west to Matala, others were left in Dongobesh, and others went to Law
qamn imuch ha qafk asmjeeg gamaday somega aa imuch gwadartai gamaway rargdaw gaway matala gaway gwand ga sunung's dung'obesh gwand gaway law
'qàmn ímùch ha qàfk àsmjéég gàmàdày sòmégà àà ímùch gwàdàrtàí gàmàwày ràrgdàw gàwày màtàlá gàwày gwànd gà súnùng''s dúng''obésh gwànd gàwày làw'
na siku nyingine waasmjega wakaja kuishi somega na wengine ambao hawaendi magharibi Matala wengine wakaachwa Dongobeshi na wengine wakaenda Musoma
For that migration in the old days with Saygilo
kwa uhamisho ule wa zamani wa saygilo
He told them "Let's scatter" and when they came
gwayesh anung'w edarda imuch aa geafk
There was a lake Mang'ola, and they finished here
makazi ya watu yakaishia huku ikamezwa na ziwa
And later a few people remained with them and scattered and finally were finished
imuch ha gwalagan gwadardaada aa gwadulan ahay
ímùch hà gwàlàgàn gwàdàrdààdà àà gwàdúlàn àhày
na badaye wachache wakabaki nao wakatawanyika hatimaye wakaishia
These people are finished, me, I haven't heard of them again
hawa watu wameisha mimi siwasikii tena
I don't know if they are still around
as ha gwasayina gid qay analdaydi
às hà gwàsàyínà gíd qày ànàldàydí
